+# 27 Estates Listings Mobile — M1 Skeleton Implementation Plan
+
+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
+
+**Goal:** Scaffold a new Expo + React Native project at `D:\Listings mobile version\`, wire Supabase + theme + navigation shell, and ship a running dev build that renders a mock Home feed. This is Milestone 1 of 4 from the design spec.
+
+**Architecture:** Greenfield Expo SDK 54 app. File-based routing via expo-router. Shared Supabase backend with the web (same project, anon key). Theme tokens lifted 1:1 from web `globals.css`. Navigation = 4-tab bar ported from web `MobileNav.tsx`.
+
+**Tech Stack:** Expo SDK 54, React Native 0.81, React 19, TypeScript (strict), expo-router v6, @supabase/supabase-js, expo-image, react-native-reanimated, @gorhom/bottom-sheet, @expo/vector-icons, react-native-svg.
+
+**Spec reference:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-15-listings-mobile-app-design.md`
+
+**What's in scope for M1:**
+- Project scaffolding at `D:\Listings mobile version\`
+- Brand assets copied from web (logo, colors)
+- Theme tokens (colors, typography, spacing, radius, shadows, motion)
+- Supabase client with AsyncStorage session persistence
+- Type generation from Supabase schema
+- `proxy-url.ts` ported verbatim from web
+- Basic UI primitives (Button, Pill, Skeleton, EmptyState)
+- 4-tab navigation shell with Browse bottom sheet
+- Placeholder screens for Home (with mock data rendering), Bookmarks, Agents, Me, property detail, category screens, auth screens
+- Running dev build on Android emulator; iOS simulator if Mac available
+- Jest + RTL wired; one smoke test covering price-format helper
+
+**Explicitly NOT in M1:** Real Supabase data in screens (mocks only), property detail full layout, search/map, filters, post wizard, agent detail, inquiries, bookmarks logic, auth flows. Those come in M2+.
+
+---
+
